main event: A bright, silvery-white light was seen near the horizon that pulsed, changed color slightly, and hovered or moved slowly up and down.
interesting points: The object was as bright as the sunlight and its motion and behavior suggested it was a genuine unidentified flying object.
The object was observed through binoculars and plotted on a chart as it hovered and moved up and down, coming on and off and pulsing rapidly before disappearing.
The witness also reported seeing six-inch-tall humanoid creatures that emerged from the side of the road and appeared to be studying a parked car before reentering the road and disappearing.
The object was estimated to be the size of a golf ball at a distance and moved at an estimated speed of 1500 mph.
The witness's car engine slowed down and the car started slowing down when the object was near, but the engine started running normally again after the object disappeared.
sighted object: a bright, silvery-white light that pulsed and changed color, and six-inch-tall humanoid creatures
witnesses: a single witness, a driver on a country road
